The '''Independent Reconfiguration Panel''' (IRP) is the independent expert on [[National Health Service (England)|National Health Service]] (NHS) service change<ref>{{cite web|url=http://whoslobbying.com/uk/independent_reconfiguration_panel|title= Independent Reconfiguration Panel|accessdate=2011-05-08}}</ref> in England. Set up in 2003, the IRP advises the [[Secretary of State for Health]] on contested proposals for health service change in England. The IRP also offers informal support and guidance to the [[NHS Scotland|NHS]] and other organisations on achieving successful change.

The IRP is made up of experienced clinicians, managers and lay members who have wide-ranging expertise in clinical healthcare, NHS management, involving the public and patients, and handling and delivering successful changes to the NHS.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.healthfornel.nhs.uk/about-us/nhs-organisations-involved/links-to-organisations-involved/?entryid41=27830|title= NHS Organisations Involved|accessdate=2011-05-08}}</ref> The panel is led by the IRP Chair and supported by the Secretariat.

